<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="103" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1438,1430,2031]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,896]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="103" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1466,1491]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
MALE. 
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1841174340" collectionCode="SMOOTH, SHINY, WITH, PART, APICALLY" location="Of" municipality="UPPeR HeAd" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" specimenCount="1">
Punctures 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:A442F619FFC5CA68FF2CFB58739DFC7C:293411D4FFC5CA6BFD92FA327003FA2F" box="[553,576,1466,1491]" municipality="UPPeR HeAd" name="Of" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">of</location>
<collectingMunicipality box="[589,717,1466,1491]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">upper head</collectingMunicipality>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[781,899,1467,1491]" class="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" family="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" genus="Mesosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">mesosoma</taxonomicName>
coarse, confluent, interspaces linear. Clypeus conspicuously concave, medially 
<collectionCode box="[532,615,1503,1527]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">smooth</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode box="[671,731,1503,1527]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">shiny</collectionCode>
<collectionCode box="[740,790,1503,1526]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">with</collectionCode>
transverse anterior sculptured 
<collectionCode box="[1139,1183,1503,1527]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">part</collectionCode>
and slight but distinct anteromedian emargination. Mandible bidentate 
<collectionCode box="[734,825,1539,1563]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">apically</collectionCode>
</materialsCitation>
, with moderate subbasal tooth beneath (
<figureCitation box="[1329,1424,1538,1563]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1632,1655]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1611]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1611]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 25–30. Zavatilla flavotegulata, ♂, Nanling. 25. Antenna; 26. Mandible; 27. Head, anterior view; 28, 29. Head and mesosoma (28, lateral view, 29, dorsal view); 30. Propodeum, dorsal view. (Photos H.-t. Zhou)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242743/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
). Flagellomere 1 length 1.0–1.2 × width, 0.8–0.95 × flagellomere 2 length. Scape with one strong ventral carina. Mesoscutum with inconspicuous lateral ridges. Mesoscutellum evenly gibbous, with median carina on anterior inclination. Tegula long, protruding over scuto-scutellar suture. Prospurs simple. Metasomal tergum 2 with long lateral felt line, 3.8–4.0 × length of that on metasomal sternum 2. Metasomal tergum 7 with median longitudinal smooth shiny line that widens and is gibbous posterad. Sternum 8 (hypopygium) transversely depressed at base, without strong lateral 
<taxonomicName authorityName="" authorityYear="1992" box="[398,483,1755,1779]" class="Insecta" family="Eccoptarthridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Carinae">carinae</taxonomicName>
. Penis valves symmetrical. Volsella with cuspis equal to or slightly longer than penis valves (
<figureCitation box="[238,425,1790,1815]" captionStart="FIGURES 46–54" captionStartId="14.[151,263,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[224,1309,260,1902]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[168,1373,253,1905]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 46–54. Zavatilla, ♂. 46–48. Z. gutrunae; 49–51. Z. flavotegulata, Nanling; 52–54. Z. xuzaifui sp. nov., holotype. 46, 49, 52. Genitalia, dorsal view; 47. Scape; 50, 53. Genitalia, lateral view; 48, 51, 54. Genitalia, ventral view. (Photos H.-t. Zhou)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242753/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Figs. 48, 51, 54</figureCitation>
), with digitus and distinct paracuspis. Parapenis much shorter than penis valve, apically thin, acuminated. 
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1841174343" collectionCode="TOOTH, SMALL, INCONSPICUOUS" location="Of" municipality="UPPeR HeAd" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" specimenCount="1">
FEMALE. Punctures 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:A442F619FFC5CA68FF2CFB58739DFC7C:293411D4FFC5CA6BFDCEF8AA70CFF8C7" box="[629,652,1826,1851]" municipality="UPPeR HeAd" name="Of" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">of</location>
<collectingMunicipality box="[668,800,1826,1851]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">upper head</collectingMunicipality>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[871,989,1827,1851]" class="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" family="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" genus="Mesosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">mesosoma</taxonomicName>
coarse, confluent, interspaces linear. Mandible bidentate, upper 
<collectionCode box="[463,520,1863,1887]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">tooth</collectionCode>
<collectionCode box="[531,592,1863,1887]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">small</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode box="[653,818,1863,1887]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">inconspicuous</collectionCode>
</materialsCitation>
. Dorsal transverse curved 
<taxonomicName authority="Of" authorityName="Of" box="[1126,1227,1862,1887]" class="Aves" family="Anatidae" genus="Carina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anseriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">carina of</taxonomicName>
clypeus with two tubercles that are larger or smaller than basomedian one. Flagellomere 1 length 1.33–1.45 × apical width, 1.54–1.6 × flagellomere 2 length, which is 0.81–0.83 × its width. Genal carina developed, ending anterad on hypostomal carina with tubercle. 
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1841174327" collectionCode="WITH, CARINA" location="Of" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" specimenCount="1">
Scutellar scale wide, 0.64–0.72 × distance between scutellar scale and inner border 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:A442F619FFC5CA68FF2CFB58739DFC7C:293411D4FFC5CA6BFA3EF83A77DFF837" box="[1413,1436,1970,1995]" name="Of" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">of</location>
posterior spiracle. Metasomal sternum 1 
<collectionCode box="[617,667,2007,2030]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">with</collectionCode>
more or less emarginated longitudinal 
<collectionCode box="[1117,1190,2007,2031]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">carina</collectionCode>
</materialsCitation>
. Metasomal tergum 2 posteriorly with fringe of dense golden (whitish) or black decumbent setae. Metasomal tergum 3 with continuous band of dense golden or whitish decumbent setae. Pygidial plate wide, 0.6–0.7 × total width of metasomal tergum 6, rounded laterally, inconspicuously carinated laterally, finely granulate or longitudinally striate in basal half.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,896]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,387,260,285]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Sex association.</emphasis>
The female of the 
<typeStatus box="[606,654,261,284]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">type</typeStatus>
species was originally described 
<collectingCountry box="[1038,1061,260,284]" name="American Samoa" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">as</collectingCountry>
<taxonomicName authority="ZAVATTARI, 1913" authorityName="Zavattari" authorityYear="1913" box="[1069,1400,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Mutilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="logei">
<emphasis box="[1069,1216,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Mutilla logei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zavattari, E." box="[1225,1400,260,284]" journalOrPublisher="Archiv für Naturgeschichte, 79 A" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" pagination="19 – 42" part="3" refId="ref10751" refString="Zavattari, E. (1913) H. Sauter's Formosa-Ausbeute. Mutillidae (Hym.). Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, 79 A (3), 19 - 42." title="H. Sauter’s Formosa-Ausbeute. Mutillidae (Hym.)" type="journal article" year="1913">Zavattari, 1913</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1413,1436,260,284]" name="American Samoa" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">as</collectingCountry>
suggested by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lelej" box="[303,445,295,320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" refId="ref9725" refString="Lelej, A. S. (2005) Catalogue of the Mutillidae (Hymenoptera) of the Oriental Region. Dalnauka, Vladivostok, 252 pp." type="book" year="2005">Lelej (2005)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="103" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,896]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,408,332,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Species included.</emphasis>
The genus includes four species (including two new ones described below): 
<taxonomicName authority="(ZAVATTARI, 1913)" authorityName="Zavattari" authorityYear="1913" baseAuthorityName="Zavattari" baseAuthorityYear="1913" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Zavatilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gutrunae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Zavatilla gutrunae</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Zavattari, E." box="[265,444,368,392]" journalOrPublisher="Archiv für Naturgeschichte, 79 A" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" pagination="19 – 42" part="3" refId="ref10751" refString="Zavattari, E. (1913) H. Sauter's Formosa-Ausbeute. Mutillidae (Hym.). Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, 79 A (3), 19 - 42." title="H. Sauter’s Formosa-Ausbeute. Mutillidae (Hym.)" type="journal article" year="1913">Zavattari, 1913</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, ♂, ♀ (China: Taiwan), 
<taxonomicName authority="(CHeN, 1957)" authorityName="Zhou &amp; Lelej &amp; Williams &amp; Liu" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="CHeN" baseAuthorityYear="1957" box="[728,1065,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Zavatilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavotegulata">
<emphasis box="[728,906,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Z. flavotegulata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Chen" box="[920,1056,367,392]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" refId="ref9303" refString="Chen, C. W. (1957) A revision of the velvet ants or Mutillidae of China (Hymenoptera). Quarterly Journal of the Taiwan Museum, 10 (3 - 4), 135 - 224, 6 pls." type="journal article" year="1957">Chen, 1957</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, ♂, ♀ (China: Zhejiang, Jiangxi, Fujian, Hunan, Guangdong, Hainan); 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhou &amp; Lelej &amp; Williams &amp; Liu, 2018" authorityName="Zhou &amp; Lelej &amp; Williams &amp; Liu" authorityYear="2018" box="[576,695,404,428]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Zavatilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xuzaifui" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[576,695,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Z. xuzaifui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[701,791,404,429]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[701,791,404,429]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
♂, ♀ (China: Guangdong, Yunnan, Hainan; Vietnam); 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhou &amp; Lelej &amp; Williams &amp; Liu, 2018" authorityName="Zhou &amp; Lelej &amp; Williams &amp; Liu" authorityYear="2018" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Zavatilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nepalensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Z. nepalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[276,366,439,464]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[276,366,439,464]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, ♀ (Nepal). Three species are known from both sexes and 
